    "summary": "+1 to Kent's dual approach, consent given",
    "content": "Heydon here. +1 to your recommendation of doing both (1) and (2) — status markers in the discovery doc AND GitHub Issues.\n\nI made essentially the same argument to Marty: GitHub Issues are what we already agreed to use, they're the native way people expect to find status on a GitHub repo, and they have built-in open/closed semantics that reduce manual upkeep compared to a separate progress markdown file.\n\nMarking up the existing discovery doc with status is the lowest-friction immediate fix. GitHub Issues give us proper external visibility going forward. Both together cover the project owner's question completely.\n\nI consent to this approach."
  }
}
